e":"Success conditions satisfied","short_title":"Satisfied","description":"{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"1qpjb\",\"text\":\"If the completion conditions have been satisfied, the piloting process is over and only needs to be documented. See steps below.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}","first_step_id":1024846,"first_step_guid":"855E3630F0F111EA8C029968456E06A2"},{"guid":"7BB140A0F0F111EA8C029968456E06A2","step_guid":"8C672A50F0F011EA8C029968456E06A2","title":"Success conditions not satisfied","short_title":"Not satisfied","description":"{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"2bva6\",\"text\":\"If the success conditions have not been satisfied, the piloting process needs to be continued. See steps below.\",\"type\":\"unstyled\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"offset\":31,\"length\":4,\"style\":\"bold\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":{}}],\"entityMap\":{}}","first_step_id":1024855,"first_step_guid":"01918F90F0F211EA8C029968456E06A2"}],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1024846,"guid":"855E3630F0F111EA8C029968456E06A2","previous_id":1024844,"previous_guid":"8C672A50F0F011EA8C029968456E06A2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8C16192A83794563AD7F3EDF05FB47CD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Completing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A51C03AB0FC64227BA23E5C9AE1F6E3D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Finish. Document what was done in each of the above steps.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"02140A5AAAC946589EDBC7E28FD2D0C2","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">In the review itself, it is important to continue to check consistency of decisions throughout the screening process, particularly for reviews which screen large numbers of studies.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1024847,"guid":"D6CB6560F0F111EA8C029968456E06A2","previous_id":1014408,"previous_guid":"9DEA7F00E85011EA977859578DCE4389","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DFCA5C333E0A4F769E3F944D5FB4E0F0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparing for Training"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"83E9493B14784AE9BFCBF98A53B1A023","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Define the success conditions for the training process.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"620783B7D1F34C6D9C8DECE79AFF1DC1","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The \"success conditions\" are the point at which the training process will have been considered sufficiently successful that it can be considered complete and the systematic review can proceed.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1024855,"guid":"01918F90F0F211EA8C029968456E06A2","previous_id":1024844,"previous_guid":"8C672A50F0F011EA8C029968456E06A2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"BC87F88C56BD471ABD6687B28ABEA37F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Revising"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4B306A63952B4507A5CEE232B611E785","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Return to Step 7. <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"3FECD920F0F211EA8C029968456E06A2","order_id":2,"type_id":22,"title":"gotostep","source":{"step_guid":"AE3A5590F0EF11EA8C029968456E06A2","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1026331,"guid":"97A38880F1AB11EAB5EA77DDD5EA7393","previous_id":1014407,"previous_guid":"9BFAE400E85011EA977859578DCE4389","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7996B3A821D643F594F76DD99FB6E850","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparing for Training"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"70981FCE84614DC496383C92776A11CE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Define the process for resolving disagreements in screening decisions. If this is arbitration by a third party, identify who this will be.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Studies of potential relevance to the objectives of a systematic reviews, as found by the search strategy, should be screened in duplicate for their eligibility. This screening process should be piloted. This protocol provides a step-by-step formula for piloting the screening process of a systematic review. The formula is also applicable to the conduct of systematic evidence maps.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">There are generally three reasons for piloting the screening process of a systematic review:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Are the eligibility criteria expressed clearly enough?<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Are the screeners on the review team interpreting the criteria consistently?<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Are there papers which should be included in the review but had not been anticipated as being relevant?<\/li><\/ol><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol presents a process for answering each of these questions in the affirmative and preparing to ensure that the screening step of the systematic review is a success, i.e. it does not result in exclusion of evidence which is relevant to the research question.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1599759162}